HEADWORD: Ensiform
<hw>En"si*form</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ensis</ets> sword + <ets>-form</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>ensiforme</ets>.]</ety> <def>Having the form of a sword blade;
sword-shaped; <as>as, an <ex>ensiform</ex> leaf</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Ensiform cartilage</b></col>, ⟦and⟧
<col><b>Ensiform process</b></col></mcol>. <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <cd>See
<er>Xiphisternum</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

